    <title>Multiplayer Use Tradeskill Containers.</title>
    <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=12724</link>
    <description>People have asked for this for ages.  How difficult would this be to create?&lt;br&gt;Interface:&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="http://i2.photobucket.com/albums/y27/EmailNBheleu/tradeskills.gif"&gt;&lt;br&gt;(Interface)&lt;br&gt;Each player puts in tradeskill items, optional plat to be given to the tradeskiller, and toggles who is to receive the end items which also toggles who can press the create button.&lt;br&gt;A check is made on each players current inventory to manufacture the item (depleting the item recipients supplies first).&lt;br&gt;If the combine fails, plat moves to the tradeskiller performing the combine and any saved items get transfered to the tradeskiller (or allow another checkbox for who receives failed item returns).&lt;br&gt;One more modification would be to display the modified skill levels of each player.&lt;br&gt;This would not replace the current player trade interface.  This would be new tradeskill interface containers in a zone or a replacement for them.&lt;br&gt;No Drop Ingredients ARE usable.&lt;br&gt;Players may also co-experiment by putting items directly into the interface with the tradeskiller hitting create.&lt;br&gt;Another modification is a cancel button!&lt;br&gt;If either player goes linkdead, items are returned to the respective players.&lt;br&gt;-----&lt;br&gt;Any other suggestions?  Please post them or thoughts.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
