    <item>
      <title>Re: Multiplayer Use Tradeskill Containers.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=12727#M12727</link>
      <description>&lt;span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;hr&gt;Healnus_Again wrote:&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;ok im confused as to what this would be used for.. like someone asks you to do a combine .. and then this interface pops up they put the items in .. all you do is hit combine? and toggle who get the finished product/salavaged failed item parts?&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;Not exactly.&lt;br&gt;This would be a new environmental tradeskill container to replace some of the functionality of the current tradeskill containers.&lt;br&gt;You could use them solo, so you are both the tradeskiller and recipient or use them with someone else and determine who will be doing the combines and reap the reward.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The reason this needs to be a tradeskill device is to permit some interaction between both parties.  The upper tier tradeskills require grossly expensive ingredients.&lt;br&gt;Giving someone those ingredients involves trust and if someone scams another it involves getting a GM or SoE support to intermediate.&lt;br&gt;Currently the policy is if you click trade, the trade is final.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Also there is some disagreement between who should get the rewards from a failed combine, since tradeskillers have to purchase that AA.  I personally feel whoever is supplying the ingredients should get them via a successful save.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
