    <item>
      <title>Re: Multiplayer Use Tradeskill Containers.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=12770#M12770</link>
      <description>It sounds similar to a mechanism in place in World of Warcraft.  You have a &amp;quot;do not trade&amp;quot; portion of the trade window, wherein the object placed there is not traded but is instead manipulated by the person performing the tradeskill on it (enchanting the object, attaching a counterweight, spurs, etc.).  Money can be exchanged for the service, and reagents are taken from the person doing the work.  Of course there's also no failure mechanism in WoW so...  All things considered I don't think it's too big of an issue in EQ.  If you get cheated on a combine the community will eventually out that tradeskiller and at least one cheat will be shut down.  If it's a really super high level combine then you need to find someone you can trust (guildy, good friend, whatever).  If you don't know any high end tradeskillers make some more friends! &lt;span&gt;:smileyvery-happy:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
